FBIS4-63106 "drsov098__a94007" FBIS-SOV-94-098-A Daily Report 20 May 1994 ANNEX Russia International Affairs Bomb Scare `False' Bomb Scare `False' LD1305163194 Warsaw PAP in English 1614 GMT 13 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY LD1305163194 Warsaw PAP English BFN [Text] Moscow, May 13 -- Staff of the Polish Embassy in Moscow was evacuated Friday afternoon and the building was checked out for a bomb allegedly planted there after the embassy received a bomb threat by telephone. A high-ranking Polish diplomat said that false bomb alarms are quite frequent in embassies in Moscow and they each time involve troublesome actions to make sure that people and buildings are safe.
